byline.original: By ANNE O'HARE McCORMICK By Telephone to THE NEW YORK TIMES

snippet: ROME, Dec. 31--Italians are superstitious about snow. Despite the discomfort and disruption of the traffic it entails, they regard the unprecedented snowfall that ends the year as a good omen....

headline.main: Europe; Italians Seem More at Ease Than Before War Began

lead_paragraph: ROME, Dec. 31--Italians are superstitious about snow. Despite the discomfort and disruption of the traffic it entails, they regard the unprecedented snowfall that ends the year as a good omen.
